<i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Clerics have to admit, they have it damn easy right now for getting pickup groups. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Ok, let me start off by saying that right now, the bitterness and loathing I feel towards Verant at what they are doing to my class is boiling and bubbling right at the surface, so please understand I don't really intend to make a personal attack on anyone here.  My comments are directed at the above quoted view in general, not at any one person specifically.<br>
<br>
Having said that...<br>
<br>
What the f**k are you smoking???<br>
<br>
Clerics have an easy time finding an exp group?? Please... Name ANY 50+ zone in the game and I can tell you how many times I've seen multiple clerics sitting on their asses at the zoneline shouting &quot;LFG&quot; for extended periods of time, while druids and shamans, mainly shamans, get snapped up for groups within 30 seconds of shouting.  There were nights I would travel from Maiden's Eye to Fungus Grove to Velks, spend a minimum of half an hour in each zone shouting &quot;55 cleric LFG&quot;...only to hear crickets chirping or have people ask me for a rez but not invite me to a group.  And when you're a cleric, having to do that much traveling without any travel spells is a damn pain in the ass.  Before I knew it, I would usually end up wasting 2+ hours travelling from zone to zone looking for a group...sometimes several nights in a row.  That's why I gave up the exp grind and was about to quit playing, but then they put in the new tradeskill stuff, so there was something to stimulate my interest enough to stay. Now, I'm almost wishing I had quit...that way I wouldn't have to watch my class treated in this fashion.<br>
<br>
Clerics aren't needed in 90% of everyday exp groups as it is now...it's going to be 100% when these changes go live.  Yes, we'll still have to mash the Complete Heal button on raids...maybe...but that's about it.<br>
<br>
I'm sorry, but if you don't play a mid-50s cleric as your main then you don't really have any right to tell clerics to stop whining because we have a monopoly on groups...because it just isn't true.<br>
<br>
There..that's off my chest...I feel better.  No hard feelings on anyone's part? Good. It just irritates me when people still think that the Holy Trinity exists and that clerics are a must have class in any group.  There is no more Holy Trinity...hasn't been since the release of Luclin and the advent of AA points. <p>Velisaris Groovenhymer<BR>
