Screw the battlecleric.<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000080><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/utaku645.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Taku645</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Soldier of the Federation</span><br>  Posts: 110<br> <font color=#70DB93>(8/23/02 9:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=339.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Straight from the Horse's ... mouth?</span><hr size=1> Rav,<br>
The way I understand it is a druid casts the spell the spell will either heal for 2950 hp or 75% (ie, 1000 hp = max heal of 750), the lower number will take effect.  if a tank has more than 3934hp the hard cap will be at 2950 and the spell won't scale any higher thus limited the effectiveness of the spell on high end raid-buffed tanks).<br>
The other school of thought is that it will heal only up to a MAX of 75% (sort of like how you can't use bind wound past a certain % of health regained).  So if a tank is below 75% health a druid would never be able to heal him above 75%.  I think the first option is the case but it could be read either way.<br>
