<hr width=100% align=left color=red>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000060><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/uashliin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ashliin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Soldier of the Federation</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#70DB93>(8/29/02 12:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=339.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: widespread beta testing</span><hr size=1> Alright, I just wanted to say a few things on this topic.  I don't play any of the 3 classes as a main, and while my husband does have a shaman as his main, I still personally think what they are doing is wrong.  First off, most shamans I have met DON'T LIKE to have to play healer.  Secondly, each class was given certains spells to start with to make them a unique class, and while most of us (especially an enchanter...my main) love having a cleric close by for thier rezzing/healing abilities, I do feel like this will make things harder on them.  I don't particularly like the thought of my cleric meleeing (honestly I think this Hammer of Judgement is the worst idea I have heard).<br>
<br>
My reasons for feeling that this could harm clerics even more comes from the following.  You have 3 groups in Kael.  When I set up groups, I try to make sure I have a cleric and druid/wiz for each group.  Then I have my heals covered and my evacs.  Now if you have druids with CH, I only need one cleric for my main group to do any rezzes that are needed.  I put a druid in my other two groups as my primary healer AND they can evac, this allows me more room for MELEES.  People to put out damage.  I have to agree with most clerics in situations like this, they will get screwed.<br>
<br>
I will NEVER allow myself to take a druid/shaman OVER a cleric.  I just feel as if Verant is taking away the uniqueness of our clerics.  If they are going to do this, they need to add something else that will continue to make our clerics unique and continue to give them the abilities needed to make them a very important part of a group, whether for exp or raids.  I don't feel that handing them a hammer and telling them to whack on a mob is an upgrade by any means.  I don't want my cleric up there swinging away, when they should be medding and healing, they can pull enough aggro with healing, they sure don't need to bring more attention to themselves in this way. <br>
<br>
Maybe they need to add some better buffs (not saying that the ones they have aren't great), maybe give clerics some buffs with more AC/HP or give them the ability to do something that NO other class can do.  Pally's get thier LoH, allow clerics something along this line, but something that would be a group spell, and something that no one else can have.  Make it such a great spell that it is only allowed once a day.  Maybe a spell called The Healing Touch (ThT), allowing a cleric to use this once a day, the spell would:  Completely heal the whole group, and give everyone full mana and stamina all at once.  They would definitely have to make sure it was a dire situation before using it, because they don't want to waste it, but yet this would continue to make a cleric unique and very wanted, knowing that they could possibly save the whole group, even if it is just once a day.<br>
<br>
I know that I was a little miffed when I heard that BL's would be getting clarity, but I knew that they nor bards would ever have my capabilities.  They are both great classes and unique in thier own ways, but they still don't take the place of an enchanter.  Even though druids and bards have other spells/songs that help with crowd control (and I love grouping with a bard that can play this part well), they will never replace an enchanter.  I think that alot of clerics feel this way, that they are being replaced.  Pally's can rez and deal damage, Shamans can now CH, best melee buffs (IMO), they have AC/HP buffs, they can haste, they have a pet, can sow, and put out some damage, especially with the pet, Druids, can now CH, have sow, damn good dots and some great nukes, can port and evac, can put out a bit of melee damage.  A cleric heals/buffs, they do have some great nukes (especially towards undead), but most don't want the cleric nuking because of the aggro, they can't sow, they can't port/evac, they don't have pets (sorry, don't consider a hammer much of a pet), so, the things they had to make them unique they no longer have.  <br>
<br>
I personally think that a shaman is already a very strong class if a person really knows how to play him/her, and that this just about makes them much more desired in a group now than a cleric.<br>
<br>
Normal groups would have been:<br>
Warrior<br>
Any Melee<br>
Cleric<br>
Enchanter<br>
Druid/Wiz<br>
Shaman <br>
<br>
Now you can almost have a group consisting of these classes and not lose a thing<br>
Warrior<br>
Melee<br>
Melee (or druid/wiz if evac needed and druid is not here for heals)<br>
Pally (for rezzes, not great, but still have it covered)<br>
Shaman/Druid (healer and if druid this covers your evacs)<br>
Enchanter<br>
<br>
This allowing a group to have 4 Melees and still have thier heals and rezzes covered.  I just don't like the idea of this, and while most people such as myself love thier clerics and won't allow this little change to affect that, there will be those that don't care, and will just take what they can get quickly as long as they have some types of heals.<br>
<br>
NOW on the FLIPSIDE of it:  I have to agree that getting clerics 50+ has been a real pain at time, and while our guild has some good clerics and a great one (Velisaris), we are always short of clerics and this would help with that problem.  We have had to call many a raid, because of the lack of clerics.  We couldn't go in with 4 groups and only ONE cleric.  This would take care of that problem, and allow us more raids.  So i'm not totally against them giving shamans and druids better heals, I just feel that they need to add something else to the cleric to continue to make them desirable and needed in exp groups and raids.  They are a class that has worked extremely hard to get to where they are, and I understand thier feelings of being jipped.<br>
<br>
Personally I think Verant could have done this a little better by ONLY giving this new upgrade in heal spells to Paladins, allowing them to CH and play healer every now and then.  Reason being that they are already a cleric class, being part cleric I would have been able to understand Verants reasoning behind it.  It would have made the paladins (who have probs with groups also) a bit more desirable to others.<br>
<br>
Alright, I have rambled on long enough, maybe I need to send Rich Waters my idea on the new cleric spell and see what they can come up with.  Not that I would necessarily want them to use that, just would like to see them give clerics something to continue thier uniqueness and continue to make them desirable to all.<br>
<br>
Clerics are my best friends =)<br>
<br>
<br>
EDIT:  Bendi that is the reason I didn't let it bother me, there were to many discussions over what they would get, and when they would get it.  When SoL first came out it was stated that BL would get clarity at lvl 39, but that was the only one they would get.  After many discussions, and rumors, it wasn't worth worrying with much, because half of the things they discussed wouldn't ever go live.<br>
<br>
